                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>During 1951, the Board of Directors of the Export-Import Bank authorized
                    $1,000,000 credits to two Bolivian mining companies to finance the cost of
                    machinery, supplies, and equipment in the United States for the expansion of
                    tungsten production. The first credit, approved <pb facs="1205" n="1183"
                        xml:id="pg_1183"/> November 1, was to Mauricio Hochschild, S. A. M. I.
                    (824.10/11–251), and the second, approved December 19, was to the Bolivian Tin
                    &amp; Tungsten Mines Corporation (824.10/12–2051). For further information, see
                    Export-Import Bank of Washington, <hi rend="italic">Thirteenth Semiannual Report
                        to Congress for the Period July–December 1951</hi> (Washington, 1952), pages
                    10–11.</p>
            </div>
